✔ Log important state changes
✔ Log failures properly
✔ Never leak sensitive data
✔ Use structured placeholders

🧠 Why Log in Service Layer?

Controller → handles HTTP
Repository → handles DB
Service → contains business logic

Business events happen here:

Money transfer started

Balance updated

Transaction created

Business rule violated

So logging belongs here.

❌ Common Wrong Logging
log.info("Transfer done " + from + to + amount);


Problems:

String concatenation (performance issue)

Hard to search

Poor structure

✅ Correct Logging Pattern

Use parameterized logging:

log.info("Transfer started | from={} | to={} | amount={}", from, to, amount);


Slf4j evaluates only if log level is enabled.

🏗 Proper Implementation
TransferService.java
@Service
@Slf4j
@RequiredArgsConstructor
public class TransferService {

    private final AccountRepository accountRepository;
    private final TransactionRepository transactionRepository;

    @Transactional
    public void transfer(String fromAcc, String toAcc, BigDecimal amount) {

        log.info("Transfer initiated | fromAccount={} | toAccount={} | amount={}",
                 fromAcc, toAcc, amount);

        Account from = accountRepository.findByAccountNumber(fromAcc)
                .orElseThrow(() -> {
                    log.warn("Source account not found | account={}", fromAcc);
                    return new RuntimeException("Source account not found");
                });

        Account to = accountRepository.findByAccountNumber(toAcc)
                .orElseThrow(() -> {
                    log.warn("Destination account not found | account={}", toAcc);
                    return new RuntimeException("Destination account not found");
                });

        if (from.getBalance().compareTo(amount) < 0) {
            log.error("Insufficient balance | account={} | balance={} | attemptedAmount={}",
                      fromAcc, from.getBalance(), amount);
            throw new InsufficientBalanceException("Insufficient balance");
        }

        from.debit(amount);
        to.credit(amount);

        log.debug("Balances updated | fromBalance={} | toBalance={}",
                  from.getBalance(), to.getBalance());

        transactionRepository.save(
                new Transaction(fromAcc, toAcc, amount)
        );

        log.info("Transfer completed successfully | fromAccount={} | toAccount={}",
                 fromAcc, toAcc);
    }
}

🎯 Log Levels Usage
INFO → Business events
Transfer initiated
Transfer completed

DEBUG → Internal details
Updated balances
SQL execution info

WARN → Recoverable issues
Account not found
Retry attempt

ERROR → Failure
Insufficient balance
Database failure

