4️⃣ Step 4 – Create Audit Aspect
AuditAspect.java
package com.bank.audit;

import lombok.RequiredArgsConstructor;
import lombok.extern.slf4j.Slf4j;
import org.aspectj.lang.ProceedingJoinPoint;
import org.aspectj.lang.annotation.*;
import org.slf4j.MDC;
import org.springframework.stereotype.Component;

import java.time.LocalDateTime;

@Aspect
@Component
@Slf4j
@RequiredArgsConstructor
public class AuditAspect {

    private final AuditRepository auditRepository;

    @Around("@annotation(audit)")
    public Object auditMethod(ProceedingJoinPoint joinPoint,
                              Audit audit) throws Throwable {

        String correlationId = MDC.get("correlationId");
        String username = "SYSTEM"; // later fetch from SecurityContext

        log.info("AUDIT START | action={}", audit.action());

        Object result = null;

        try {
            result = joinPoint.proceed();

            auditRepository.save(
                    AuditLog.builder()
                            .action(audit.action())
                            .username(username)
                            .correlationId(correlationId)
                            .timestamp(LocalDateTime.now())
                            .build()
            );

            log.info("AUDIT SUCCESS | action={}", audit.action());

        } catch (Exception ex) {

            auditRepository.save(
                    AuditLog.builder()
                            .action(audit.action() + "_FAILED")
                            .username(username)
                            .correlationId(correlationId)
                            .timestamp(LocalDateTime.now())
                            .build()
            );

            log.error("AUDIT FAILED | action={} | error={}",
                      audit.action(), ex.getMessage());

            throw ex;
        }

        return result;
    }
}

5️⃣ Step 5 – Use in Service
TransferService.java
@Audit(action = "MONEY_TRANSFER")
@Transactional
public void transfer(String from, String to, BigDecimal amount) {
    // business logic
}


No audit code inside service.

Clean and professional.

🧠 What Happens Internally?

When method is called:

Spring creates proxy
Proxy calls → AuditAspect
Aspect wraps method execution
Audit saved before/after execution

This is how Spring AOP works.

🎯 Logging vs Audit (Important)
Logging	Audit
Technical info	Business action
Can be disabled	Must be stored
Temporary	Permanent record
Used for debugging	Used for compliance
🧠 Interview Deep Questions
Q: Why use @Around instead of @Before?

Because:

We want success + failure logging

We need access to result

We need try/catch

Q: What happens if audit save fails?

In production:

Use separate transaction (REQUIRES_NEW)

Or async event

Avoid blocking main transaction

🔥 Advanced: Use Separate Transaction for Audit
@Transactional(propagation = Propagation.REQUIRES_NEW)
public void saveAudit(AuditLog log) {
    auditRepository.save(log);
}


Prevents rollback of main transaction affecting audit.

