Audit Entity (Production-Grade Design)

The Audit Entity represents permanent business audit records stored in the database.

In banking/trading systems, this table is:

Never deleted

Used for compliance

Used in investigations

Often write-heavy

🧠 What Should an Audit Entity Contain?

Minimum required fields:

✔ id
✔ action (business event)
✔ username
✔ correlationId
✔ timestamp
✔ status (SUCCESS / FAILED)

Advanced (recommended):

✔ entityType
✔ entityId
✔ requestPayload (optional)
✔ responseStatus
✔ ipAddress

🏗 Clean & Scalable Audit Entity
AuditLog.java
package com.bank.audit;

import jakarta.persistence.*;
import lombok.*;

import java.time.LocalDateTime;

@Entity
@Table(name = "audit_logs",
       indexes = {
           @Index(name = "idx_correlation", columnList = "correlationId"),
           @Index(name = "idx_timestamp", columnList = "timestamp"),
           @Index(name = "idx_username", columnList = "username")
       })
@Getter
@Setter
@NoArgsConstructor
@AllArgsConstructor
@Builder
public class AuditLog {

    @Id
    @GeneratedValue(strategy = GenerationType.IDENTITY)
    private Long id;

    // Business action (TRANSFER, ACCOUNT_CREATE, etc.)
    @Column(nullable = false, length = 100)
    private String action;

    // SUCCESS / FAILED
    @Column(nullable = false, length = 20)
    private String status;

    // Logged-in user
    @Column(length = 100)
    private String username;

    // Correlation ID for tracing
    @Column(length = 100)
    private String correlationId;

    // Which entity is affected (optional but powerful)
    @Column(length = 100)
    private String entityType;

    @Column(length = 100)
    private String entityId;

    // Optional: request payload (be careful with sensitive data)
    @Lob
    @Column(columnDefinition = "TEXT")
    private String requestPayload;

    private LocalDateTime timestamp;
}

🧠 Why Add Indexes?

Audit tables grow very fast.

You will frequently query:

By correlationId

By username

By date range

Without indexes → slow queries in production.

